{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Depending on the specific properties of the problems, we recommend the DSC or IoU (default recommendation), the F β score (preferred when there is a preference for either false positive (FP) or false negative (FN)) or the centerline Dice similarity coefficient (clDice; for tubular structures).",
    "Details can be found in subprocess S6 for selecting overlap-based metrics (Extended Data Fig. 6).",
    "overlap-based metrics include shape unawareness and limitations when dealing with small structures or high size variability 27.",
    "Our general recommendation is therefore to complement an overlap-based metric with a boundary-based metric.",
    "If annotation imprecisions should be compensated for (FP2.5.7), our default recommendation is the normalized surface distance (NSD)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "overlap-based metrics include shape unawareness and limitations when dealing with small structures or high size variability 27."
  ]
}